  "title": "chore(ts-migration): adds api extractor for type definitions",
  "body": "This pull request replaces the current experimental type definitions system by api extractor. Keep in mind, with this pull request, type definitions will be generated on the stable tag ( instead of the experimental one ). \r\n\r\nNow, once you run `yarn:build` the type definitions will be generated for the package:\r\n\r\n```\r\nWriting package typings: /Users/nunomaduro/Algolia/instantsearch.js/dist/index.d.ts\r\nWarning: temp/types/index.d.ts:5:5 - (ae-forgotten-export) The symbol \"InstantSearchOptions\" needs to be exported by the entry point index.d.ts\r\nWarning: temp/types/index.d.ts:5:5 - (ae-forgotten-export) The symbol \"InstantSearch\" needs to be exported by the entry point index.d.ts\r\nWarning: temp/types/index.d.ts:7:5 - (ae-forgotten-export) The symbol \"snippet\" needs to be exported by the entry point index.d.ts\r\nWarning: temp/types/index.d.ts:8:5 - (ae-forgotten-export) The symbol \"highlight\" needs to be exported by the entry point index.d.ts\r\nWarning: temp/types/index.d.ts:9:5 - (ae-forgotten-export) The symbol \"insights\" needs to be exported by the entry point index.d.ts\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe errors are normal, mean that API Extractor is doing his job. They are going to be addressed in a different pull request.",
